Earlier, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) issued travel warnings for Texas and Arizona after the states passed immigration laws requiring local law enforcement to arrest people for immigration violations, which the ACLU believes will contribute to further racial profiling.
Travel advisories are typically issued by the State Department for other countries, but recently advocacy groups have deployed the measure in response to specific laws and trends within the US.
