Brooks said the rumor around town was that Hester had slept with Malcom&#39;s wife, Dorothy, and that the baby she was carrying was not her husband&#39;s.
On July 25, 1946, Loy Harrison, a prominent white landowner, paid $600 to break Malcom out of prison, according to the FBI.
He was accompanied to prison by Dorothy and her cousins Mae Murray and George Dorsey.
But as they walked away from the jail and near Moore&#39;s Ford Bridge, a lynch mob surrounded the car.
&quot;As it turns out, it was Harrison who prepared and ordered the killings,&quot; concludes an FBI report.
&quot;It is also apparent that there was a conspiracy between state and local law enforcement, who not only participated in the killings, removing evidence and covering up the identities of witnesses.&quot;
Brooks put it even more succinctly.
