Amazon&#39;s Comrade Detective, meanwhile, evokes a different kind of nostalgia: the Cold War revival of The Americans, the movie Atomic Blonde, and even GLOW, with its East vs. West wrestling iconography .
The comedy created by Brian Gatewood and Alessandro Tanaka and directed by Rhys Thomas claims to be a found TV series: an eighties Romanian drama with the two policemen as friends, two officers from Bucharest who fight for truth, atheism and the Fighting the way of Marxism-Leninism.
The lead roles - a hardened Gregor and an idealistic Iosef - are played by Florin Piersic Jr. and Corneliu Ulici, with dialogue dubbed into English by Channing Tatum (also an executive producer) and Joseph Gordon-Levitt.
It&#39;s a brilliant idea.
But it&#39;s not much more than an idea.
