When asked about the odd timing of all these things, Dewey-Hagborg said that &quot;things happen for a reason&quot;.
In an artistic statement inscribed on the gallery wall, Manning, with her oversized signature below it (the &quot;i&quot; in her family name is followed by a heart), called for an end to &quot;the automatic fragmentation that has been based on gender, race, sexuality and culture. &quot;
